  "prompt": "What should you engrave on promise rings?",
  "response": "Engraving on promise rings can be a deeply personal and meaningful gesture. The right words or symbols depend on your relationship and what you want to convey. Here are some ideas to consider:\n\n### Personal Messages\n1. **Names or Initials**: Simple and timeless. \n2. **Dates**: The date you met, started dating, or promised each other.\n3. **A Short Phrase or Quote**:\n   - \"Forever Yours\"\n   - \"My One & Only\"\n   - \"To the Moon\"\n   - \"Always\"\n\n### Special Words or Sayings\n1. **Insider Jokes or Nicknames**: Something that\u2019s uniquely yours.\n2. **Love Message**: \"I Promise\" or \"Endless Love\"\n3. **Symbolic Words**: \"Infinity\" or \"Soulmates\"\n\n### Foreign Languages \n1. **French**: \"Toujours\" (Always)\n2. **Spanish**: \"Para Siempre\" (Forever)\n3. **Latin**: \"Semper\" (Always)\n\n### Coordinates \n1. **Location**: Where you met or a place special to you both.\n\n### Symbols\n1. **Hearts**\n2. **Infinity Symbol**\n3. **Lock and Key**\n\nUltimately, the engraving should reflect your relationship and the unique bond you share.",
